# Button

The Button component provides an interactive button element with multiple variants, sizes, and states.

## Examples

### Basic Button

<div style="display: flex; gap: var(--lt-spacing-3); margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0; flex-wrap: wrap;">
  <lt-button>Default</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="primary">Primary</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="secondary">Secondary</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="danger">Danger</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="ghost">Ghost</lt-button>
</div>

```html
<lt-button>Default</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="primary">Primary</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="secondary">Secondary</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="danger">Danger</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="ghost">Ghost</lt-button>
```

### Sizes

<div style="display: flex; gap: var(--lt-spacing-3); align-items: center; margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0; flex-wrap: wrap;">
  <lt-button size="sm" variant="primary">Small</lt-button>
  <lt-button size="md" variant="primary">Medium</lt-button>
  <lt-button size="lg" variant="primary">Large</lt-button>
</div>

```html
<lt-button size="sm" variant="primary">Small</lt-button>
<lt-button size="md" variant="primary">Medium</lt-button>
<lt-button size="lg" variant="primary">Large</lt-button>
```

### With Icons

<div style="display: flex; gap: var(--lt-spacing-3); margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0; flex-wrap: wrap;">
  <lt-button variant="primary" icon="save">Save</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="secondary" icon="download">Download</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="danger" icon="trash">Delete</lt-button>
</div>

```html
<lt-button variant="primary" icon="save">Save</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="secondary" icon="download">Download</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="danger" icon="trash">Delete</lt-button>
```

### Loading State

<div style="display: flex; gap: var(--lt-spacing-3); margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0; flex-wrap: wrap;">
  <lt-button variant="primary" loading>Loading...</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="secondary" loading>Please wait</lt-button>
</div>

```html
<lt-button variant="primary" loading>Loading...</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="secondary" loading>Please wait</lt-button>
```

### Disabled State

<div style="display: flex; gap: var(--lt-spacing-3); margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0; flex-wrap: wrap;">
  <lt-button variant="primary" disabled>Disabled</lt-button>
  <lt-button variant="secondary" disabled>Disabled</lt-button>
</div>

```html
<lt-button variant="primary" disabled>Disabled</lt-button>
<lt-button variant="secondary" disabled>Disabled</lt-button>
```

### Full Width

<div style="margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0;">
  <lt-button variant="primary" full-width>Full Width Button</lt-button>
</div>

```html
<lt-button variant="primary" full-width>Full Width Button</lt-button>
```

## Properties

| Property | Type | Default | Description |
|----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `variant` | `'default' \| 'primary' \| 'secondary' \| 'danger' \| 'ghost'` | `'default'` | Visual style variant |
| `size` | `'sm' \| 'md' \| 'lg'` | `'md'` | Button size |
| `icon` | `string` | - | Icon name to display |
| `loading` | `boolean` | `false` | Shows loading spinner |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables the button |
| `full-width` | `boolean` | `false` | Makes button full width |

## Events

| Event | Detail | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `lt-click` | `MouseEvent` | Fired when button is clicked |

## Usage

```typescript
import '@latty/web/button';

const button = document.querySelector('lt-button');
button.addEventListener('lt-click', () => {
  console.log('Button clicked!');
});
```

## Accessibility

- Uses native `<button>` element
- Supports keyboard navigation (Space and Enter keys)
- Includes proper ARIA attributes when loading or disabled
- Focus visible styles for keyboard navigation

<script is:inline type="module">
